<br>
as for the mana... how many hps does a lvl 40-45 warrior type have? i know that i can do up to 4000dd before i have to med... and as for casters lacking the hps.. a warrior that cant move cant hurt my hps =) hehe.<br>
basically, if you have 2 wizards throwing gravity fluxes out the wazoo and doing bonds of force (ae snare) along with one or two necros fearing and mezing people, a magician or two with earth pets (quad for 50..) that can actually kill a warrior of the mages level and an enchanter lowering all the other groups resistances and you have a pretty powerful group.<br>
<br>
basically: 2 wiz (6k-8kdd), 1 necro (5-7kdot), 1 enchanter(clarity/resistances/fears/ae mez), 2magicians(tanks/5-7kdd) can pretty easily wipe out any melee based group. the damage numbers are based on casters in the 40-45 range.  i doubt any group now matter how balanced can take 16-22k damage +pet damage... healers dont matter as they would be executed by the two wizards in the beginning =).  bottom line, pure casters are the master of damage, sure we have to meditate between fights but when the enemy is dead meditating is safe =P<br>
<br>
personally, i think this is a well balanced group.<br>
